    think='Looking at the log, I can see something very important. When the fiel
d is tapped after erasing, the element attributes show:\n\n```\nhintText=服务器
地址\nhttp://localhost:3000/api/v1\n```\n\nAnd the error text is still visible:\
n```\naccessibilityText=请输入服务器地址\n```\n\nAnd critically, the save button
is still:\n```\nenabled=false\nclickable=false\n```\n\nThis means that after tap
ping the field, the text is STILL empty and the error "请输入服务器地址" is stil
l showing. But we then do `inputText: "http://10.0.2.2:3001/api/v1"`. After that
, the save button should become enabled. But looking at the log when save is tap
ped:\n\n```\nTapping on element: UiElement(treeNode=TreeNode(attributes={text=, 
accessibilityText=保存配置, hintText=, ... enabled=false, ... class=android.widg
et.Button}, ...\n```\n\nThe button is STILL disabled after `inputText`!\n\nThis 
is very strange. Why would `inputText` not update the controller/state?\n\nWait,
I just noticed something in the log. The field shows:\n```\nhintText=服务器地址\
nhttp://localhost:3000/api/v1\n```\n\nThis is the HINT text, not the actual text
. The actual text (`text=`) is empty. This suggests the field is empty and showi
ng the hint.\n\nBut then `inputText` types "http://10.0.2.2:3001/api/v1". After 
that, when we tap save, the button is still disabled. This means either:\n1. `in
putText` didn\'t work\n2. The state wasn\'t updated\n\nLet me look at the log be
tween `inputText` and `tapOn save`:\n\n```\nInput text http://10.0.2.2:3001/api/
v1... COMPLETED\nTap on "保存配置"... \n```\n\nThere\'s no gap. `inputText` comp
leted and then save was tapped. But the button is disabled.\n\nWait, let me look
more carefully at the `inputText` completion log:\n\n```\n15:35:44.007 [ INFO] m
aestro.cli.runner.MaestroCommandRunner.invoke: Input text http://10.0.2.2:3001/a
pi/v1 COMPLETED\n15:35:44.007 [ INFO] maestro.cli.runner.MaestroCommandRunner.in
voke: Tap on "保存配置" RUNNING\n```\n\nAnd then:\n```\n15:35:44.092 [ INFO] mae
stro.Maestro.tap-BUbHBYE: Tapping on element:  UiElement(treeNode=TreeNode(attri
butes={text=, accessibilityText=保存配置, hintText=, ignoreBoundsFiltering=false
, resource-id=, clickable=false, bounds=[335,683][986,809], enabled=false, focus
ed=false, checked=false, scrollable=false, selected=false, class=android.widget.
Button}, children=[], clickable=false, enabled=false, focused=false, checked=fal
se, selected=false)\n```\n\nSo immediately after `inputText` completes, the save
button is still disabled. This strongly suggests that `inputText` didn\'t actual
ly update the field text.\n\nWhy would `inputText` not work? Let me think...\n\n
Actually, I wonder if the issue is with the `eraseText: 100`. In Maestro, `erase
Text` sends backspace key events. But looking at the log, `eraseText` took about
7-8 seconds. That\'s normal for 100 backspaces.\n\nBut wait - what if `eraseText
` somehow puts the field into a bad state? For example, if the field loses focus
during erasing, or if the keyboard is dismissed.\n\nActually, looking at the log
after `eraseText`:\n```\n15:35:40.322 [ INFO] maestro.cli.runner.MaestroCommandR
unner.invoke: Assert that "保存成功，新配置已生效" is not visible COMPLETED\n15:
35:40.938 [ INFO] maestro.cli.runner.MaestroCommandRunner.invoke: Tap on id: ser
ver_base_url_field RUNNING\n```\n\nThere\'s a gap of about 0.6 seconds between t
he assertion and the tap. During this time, maybe the keyboard was dismissed?\n\
nBut then we tap the field, which should bring up the keyboard again. And `input
Text` should type into the focused field.\n\nWait, I just noticed something. Loo
king at the first `inputText: not-a-url`:\n```\n15:35:27.521 [ INFO] maestro.cli
.runner.MaestroCommandRunner.invoke: Input text not-a-url RUNNING\n15:35:27.521 
[ INFO] maestro.Maestro.inputText: Inputting text: not-a-url\n15:35:29.946 [ INF
O] maestro.cli.runner.MaestroCommandRunner.invoke: Input text not-a-url COMPLETE
D\n```\n\nIt took about 2.4 seconds for 10 characters. That\'s about 240ms per c
haracter.\n\nThen `eraseText: 100` took about 7.8 seconds (from 15:35:29 to 15:3
5:37). That\'s about 78ms per backspace.\n\nThen `inputText: http://10.0.2.2:300
1/api/v1` (25 characters) took about 3.3 seconds (from 15:35:40 to 15:35:44). Th
at\'s about 132ms per character.\n\nThe timing seems reasonable. So `inputText` 
should have typed the text.\n\nBut why is the button still disabled?\n\nOH WAIT.
I just realized something. Look at the `server_url_tool.dart`:\n\n```dart\n_cont
roller.addListener(() {\n  context.read<DevToolsCubit>().onUrlChanged(_controlle
r.text);\n});\n```\n\nThis listener is added in `initState`. But `context.read<D
evToolsCubit>()` in `initState`... is this safe?\n\nIn Flutter, `context.read<T>
()` in `initState` is generally safe because it just looks up the provider in th
e ancestor tree. It doesn\'t subscribe to changes. So this should be fine.\n\nBu
t wait - what if the `BlocProvider` is not yet in the tree when `initState` is c
alled? No, `initState` is called after the widget is inserted into the tree, so 
ancestors are available.\n\nHmm, let me think about this differently. What if th
e issue is that Maestro\'s `inputText` types the text, but the Flutter `TextFiel
d` doesn\'t update the controller properly because of some issue with the custom
`SwTextField` or the focus node?\n\nActually, let me look at `SwTextField` again
:\n\n```dart\nreturn Semantics(\n  identifier: identifier,\n  label: labelText ?
? hintText,\n  textField: true,\n  child: TextField(\n    controller: controller
,\n    focusNode: focusNode,\n    ...\n    enableInteractiveSelection: true,\n  
 decoration: InputDecoration(\n      ...\n    ),\n  ),\n);\n```\n\nThis looks co
rrect. `TextField` receives `controller` and `focusNode`.\n\nWait, I just realiz
ed something. In the Maestro log, when the field is tapped, it shows:\n```\nhint
Text=服务器地址\nhttp://localhost:3000/api/v1\n```\n\nThis is the hint text of t
he `TextField`, which is `hintText: \'http://localhost:3000/api/v1\'` from `serv
er_url_tool.dart`. But wait, the `SwTextField` in `server_url_tool.dart` has:\n`
``dart\nhintText: \'http://localhost:3000/api/v1\',\n```\n\nSo the hint text is 
always "http://localhost:3000/api/v1". This is NOT the actual text in the field.
\n\nAfter `inputText: "http://10.0.2.2:3001/api/v1"`, the actual text should be 
"http://10.0.2.2:3001/api/v1". But the Maestro log shows the button is still dis
abled.\n\nLet me check if there\'s something wrong with the `onUrlChanged` logic
. In `dev_tools_cubit.dart`:\n```dart\nvoid onUrlChanged(String url) {\n  emit(s
tate.copyWith(\n    serverBaseUrl: url,\n    urlError: _validateUrl(url),\n    s
aveSuccess: false,\n  ));\n}\n```\n\nAnd `_validateUrl`:\n```dart\nString _valid
ateUrl(String url) {\n  final trimmed = url.trim();\n  if (trimmed.isEmpty) retu
rn \'请输入服务器地址\';\n  if (!trimmed.startsWith(RegExp(r\'^https?://\'))) {\
n    return \'请输入有效的 HTTP/HTTPS URL\';\n  }\n  return \'\';\n}\n```\n\nFor
"http://10.0.2.2:3001/api/v1", `trimmed` is "http://10.0.2.2:3001/api/v1". It st
arts with `http://`. So `_validateUrl` returns `\'\'`. The state should have `ur
lError: \'\'`.\n\nThen in `server_url_tool.dart`:\n```dart\nisDisabled: state.ur
lError.isNotEmpty || state.serverBaseUrl.trim().isEmpty,\n```\n\nWith `urlError:
\'\'` and `serverBaseUrl: \'http://10.0.2.2:3001/api/v1\'`, `isDisabled` should 
be `false`.\n\nSo the button SHOULD be enabled. Why is it disabled in the Maestr
o test?\n\nLet me look at whether the Maestro `inputText` actually changes the t
ext. Maybe there\'s a bug where `inputText` doesn\'t work after `eraseText` in F
lutter TextFields.\n\nActually, I just thought of another possibility. In the lo
g, when the field is tapped after erasing:\n```\nbounds=[282,252][1038,858]\n```
\n\nThis is a large area. The actual `EditText` inside has bounds `[335,396][986
,638]`. The `TextField` has a `prefixIcon` (the `Icon(Icons.link)`). Maybe Maest
ro\'s `inputText` is typing into the wrong element?\n\nWait, `inputText` types i
nto the currently focused text field. The log shows that after tapping, the inne
r `EditText` has `focused=true`. So the field is focused.\n\nBut then `inputText
` types, and after that, the save button is still disabled. This is very strange
.\n\nLet me try a different approach. Instead of trying to debug why `inputText`
isn\'t working after `eraseText`, I\'ll restructure the flow to avoid this patte
rn.\n\nIn the original `edit_server_url.yaml`, they use:\n```yaml\n- tapOn:\n   
id: "server_base_url_field"\n- inputText: "http://192.168.1.100:3000/api/v1"\n- 
tapOn: "保存配置"\n```\n\nThen for the second edit:\n```yaml\n- tapOn:\n    id: 
"server_base_url_field"\n- inputText: "http://example.com:8080/api/v2"\n- tapOn:
"保存配置"\n```\n\nNotice they NEVER use `eraseText` in the original flow. The f
ocus listener selects all text when the field is tapped, so `inputText` replaces
the old text automatically.\n\nIn my flow, I used `eraseText: 100` which might b
e causing issues. Let me restructure the flow to NOT use `eraseText`. Instead, I
\'ll just tap the field (which selects all) and then type the new text.\n\nWait,
but for the empty URL test, I need to clear the field. How can I do that without
`eraseText`?\n\nActually, looking at the BDD feature:\n```gherkin\nScenario: Emp
ty URL shows error\n  Given the dev tools drawer is open\n  When the user clears
the input field\n  Then the input border should turn red\n```\n\n"Clears the inp
ut field" - in Maestro, this could be done by selecting all and replacing with e
mpty text. But Maestro doesn\'t have a "select all" command.\n\nAlternatively, I
can type a valid URL first, then tap the field (which selects all), then... I ca
n\'t type empty text with `inputText`.\n\nHmm, maybe I should separate the inval
id and empty URL tests into different flows, or just test invalid URL in E2E and
leave empty URL to widget tests.\n\nActually, let me try a different approach fo
r clearing. I\'ll use `eraseText` but with a smaller number, and make sure the f
ield has focus. Or I can just test invalid URL and skip empty URL in the E2E flo
w.\n\nLet me restructure the `invalid_server_url.yaml`:\n\n```yaml\n# 打开 DevTo
ols 抽屉\n- tapOn:\n    id: "dev_tools_toggle_button"\n- assertVisible: "服务器
地址"\n\n# 输入无效 URL，应出现格式错误提示\n- tapOn:\n    id: "server_base_url_
field"\n- inputText: "not-a-url"\n- assertVisible: "请输入有效的 HTTP/HTTPS URL"
\n\n# 尝试保存无效配置——由于按钮被禁用，不应出现成功提示\n- tapOn: "保存配置"\n-
